{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"typeEnsure"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"type","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GType","text":"GType"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In theory, simply calling the type’s "},{"code":"_get_type()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method (or using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the corresponding macro) is supposed take care of this. However,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"_get_type()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" methods are often marked "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_GNUC_CONST"},{"type":"text","text":" for performance"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reasons, even though this is technically incorrect (since"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"G_GNUC_CONST","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" requires that the function not have side effects,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which "},{"code":"_get_type()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" methods do on the first call). As a result, if"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you write a bare call to a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_get_type()"},{"text":" macro, it may get optimized","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"out by the compiler. Using "},{"code":"g_type_ensure()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" guarantees that the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type’s "},{"code":"_get_type()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method is called."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensures that the indicated "},{"code":"type","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" has been registered with the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type system, and its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_class_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" method has been run."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/typeEnsure(type:)"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeensure(type:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Function","symbolKind":"func","externalID":"s:10GLibObject10typeEnsure0C0ySu_tF","title":"typeEnsure(type:)","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"typeEnsure","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"type","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GType","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GType","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/typeEnsure(type:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeensure(type:)","title":"typeEnsure(type:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Ensures that the indicated ","type":"text"},{"code":"type","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has been registered with the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"type system, and its "},{"code":"_class_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method has been run.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"typeEnsure","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"type","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GType","text":"GType","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],